1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,500
In the same room there was a toilet

2
00:00:01,583 --> 00:00:03,250
The toilet door was open twenty-four hours

3
00:00:04,333 --> 00:00:08,041
You could relieve yourself whenever you wanted

4
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:10,958
But in the morning you had to wake up

5
00:00:11,416 --> 00:00:13,875
For prayer at the right time

6
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:15,625
After the call to prayer, you prayed

7
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:18,791
Anyone could be the imam and we would pray

8
00:00:19,416 --> 00:00:20,833
Interviewer: Was the imam one of the prisoners?

9
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,166
Yes, one of the prisoners

10
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:24,833
Interviewer: Did they come to pray with you? Witness: Who do you mean?

11
00:00:25,083 --> 00:00:26,541
Interviewer: The jailers? Witness: No

12
00:00:26,916 --> 00:00:29,791
The jailers prayed, even those who hadn’t been praying

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,583
Interviewer: Not the prisoners? Rather the jailer?

14
00:00:31,666 --> 00:00:33,916
No, we didn’t see him

15
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:38,958
Only if there was an interrogation with you, or they wanted information from you, he would come to take you

16
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:41,500
Otherwise you stayed in the prison

17
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:45,708
But at the dawn prayer he would come to wake you; even if you were asleep he would knock on the door

18
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:48,250
For prayer… prayer… he calls you to prayer

19
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:54,625
Interviewer: Regarding the toilet, were you able to take your time when you relieved yourself?

20
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:57,541
No, we were not comfortable—since we entered we did not feel comfortable

21
00:00:57,666 --> 00:00:59,291
Because you do not know your fate

22
00:00:59,416 --> 00:01:02,208
Someone would tell you they would execute you

23
00:01:02,291 --> 00:01:05,250
Another would say they would kill you, and another would say they would cut off your hand

24
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:08,666
You do not know what your fate is

25
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:16,458
Interviewer: The water in the toilet—was it hot, warm, or cold?

26
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:18,791
No, it was tank water, from the tank

27
00:01:19,208 --> 00:01:21,583
Interviewer: Was it always available, or did it get cut off?

28
00:01:21,958 --> 00:01:24,500
It was from the tank, whenever you opened the tap it was there

29
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:27,791
Cleaning was required, and what did we even have that needed cleaning in the first place

30
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:29,375
You didn’t have cigarettes

31
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:31,125
Only leftover food

32
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:34,916
And the extra water and food, that was the cleaning they had

33
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:36,333
You had nothing with you

34
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:38,208
Interviewer: Was there a garbage container?

35
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:40,000
There were bags you could tie shut

36
00:01:40,541 --> 00:01:46,666
When they gave you food, you tied the bag and threw it at the door, and he would take it

37
00:01:46,958 --> 00:01:49,041
Interviewer: While you were in this place, did you have cleaning supplies?

38
00:01:49,166 --> 00:01:53,333
Like soap, dishwashing liquid, or disinfectants?

39
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:58,375
No disinfectants, just soap when leaving the toilet

40
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:01,833
Interviewer: Was the soap enough for you? Witness: It was enough

41
00:02:03,083 --> 00:02:05,916
There were two bars, one for washing hands

42
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:09,250
And for whoever wanted, like one time

43
00:02:09,458 --> 00:02:14,208
One prisoner told them, I’m <i>janoub</i> [ritually impure], so they told him, Go shower

44
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:17,375
It was the same place used as both the shower and the toilet

45
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,208
And there were two towels as well

46
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:25,875
Interviewer: For showering, was it whenever you wanted?

47
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Not whenever you wanted, maybe every two or three days someone would shower

48
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,625
Interviewer: There was no shower schedule? Witness: No, no

49
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:39,041
Interviewer: You were inside the cell and the toilet was with you too?

50
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:40,500
The toilet was the same place for showering

51
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:44,333
Interviewer: No one had authority over you in this matter, you could do it freely?

52
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:45,375
Yes, we could do it freely
